## Domain knowledge docs

List any Confluence pages, URLs, or file paths that give the assistant domain context. These are read at intake to help ask smarter questions.

```yaml
domainDocs:
  - "[https://your-org.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/TEAM/pages/...] (optional)"
  - "[https://internal-docs.example.com/product-overview] (optional)"
```

---

## Output preferences

```yaml
defaultDraftDepth: "standard"   # minimal | standard | comprehensive
```

**What this means:**
- `minimal` — sketches, outlines, candidate options. Ask before full artefacts.
- `standard` *(recommended)* — reasonable artefacts at each step, declared upfront.
- `comprehensive` — full artefacts at every step unless you say otherwise.

Override per artefact any time by saying so in chat.

---

## Commands

These commands are always available in any BA Assistant session:

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `/next` | Top 3 next actions by urgency across all active workstreams |
| `/status` | Full current state — triple output: chat + canvas + HTML snapshot |
| `/canvas` | Generate or refresh the interactive project canvas |
| `/report` | Full structured report — all outputs in one document |
| `/snapshot` | Living tracker snapshot |
| `/publish-status` | Publish status page to Confluence |
| `/retro` | Trigger a retrospective |
| `/metrics` | Pull all four metrics with per-scope breakdown |
| `/reanchor` | Re-read state files when the assistant has drifted in a long thread |
| `/validate-state` | Read-only drift report — diffs files, checks Jira, flags stale pages |
| `/wrap` | End-of-session closeout — promote items, refresh workboard, suggest new chat |
| `/workboard` | Cross-initiative priorities view |
| `/setup` | Re-run the first-run wizard to reconfigure |

