## Status page format

When publishing status pages to Confluence, the assistant will use the Status Page Standard Format defined in `references/status-page-format.md`. Required sections:

1. Header (date, stage, charter, PM, BA, tech lead)
2. Where We Are
3. What Was Achieved Last Week
4. What Is Planned This Week
5. Feature Status
6. Critical Path
7. Outstanding Blockers
8. Cohort / Delivery Model
9. Living Tracker (knowns, unknowns, assumptions, risks, dependencies, decisions)
10. Confidence Scores
11. Key Artefacts

---

## Jira integration notes

If Jira MCP is configured, the assistant will:
- Search for existing tickets at intake
- Create stories, spikes, and bugs in your configured project
- Sync ticket statuses into `status-data.json`

If Jira MCP is not configured, the assistant generates ticket content as draft text that you can copy-paste. See `SETUP.md` for MCP setup instructions.

